{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Outer membrane channel protein MctB in Mycobacterium tuberculosis is part of a Cu resistance mechanism that ensures low intracellular Cu levels in the bacterium. Human resistance to bacteria, mediated via IFN-gamma mediated activation of macrophages, may involve the use of reactive Cu(1) in the presence of hydrogen peroxide, since activated Cu is toxic to bacteria. IFN-gamma stimulates the trafficking of the Cu transporter ATP7a to the vesicles that fuse with phagosomes and these phagosomes are found to have a high Cu content and an increased bactericidal activity against E.coli. Using MctB, Mycobacterium tuberculosis may limit the amount of excess Cu within it whole in the host [[cite:PUB00075654]]. MctB is involved copper resistance, but it is unclear whether it plays a direct role in copper efflux [[cite:PUB00087495]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "8au6", "name" "Structure of Corynebacterium glutamicum Cg1604, a cell division regulator"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF11382" "Copper transport outer membrane protein, MctB"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Copper transporter MctB", "short" "MctB"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 6, "proteomes" 1141, "taxa" 3477, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3349, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3265, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2614}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR021522", :literature {"PUB00075654" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Wolschendorf F" "Ackart D" "Shrestha TB" "Hascall-Dove L" "Nolan S" "Lamichhane G" "Wang Y" "Bossmann SH" "Basaraba RJ" "Niederweis M."], "ISO_journal" "Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1009261108", "medline_journal" "Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A", "title" "Copper resist